litelang is an interpreted programming language which is supposed to be primitive in design and in implementation.

== Features ==

=== Data types ===

* Boolean (BOOL_T)
* Byte (BBYTE_T and XBYTE_T)
* Integer (INT_T)
* Double (DOUBLE_T)
* Symbol (SYMBOL_T)

=== Blocks ===

* If ('if', 'elif', 'else')
* While (with 'break' and 'continue' support)
* Function

=== Operations ===

* Arithmetic (+, -, *, /, %)
* Bit (&, |, ~, ^, >>, <<)
* Logic (<, >, <=, >=, ==, !=, not, and, or, xor)
* Assign (=, +=, -=, *=, /=, %=)


